Global Negative Pressure Wound Therapy Unit (NPWTU) Market Insights
Negative Pressure Wound Therapy Unit (NPWTU) Market size was valued at USD 2.4 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 4.1 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 7.5% from 2024 to 2030.

Negative Pressure Wound Therapy Unit (NPWTU) Market Overview
The global Negative Pressure Wound Therapy Unit (NPWTU) market is valued at USD 2.12 billion in 2024 and is expected to reach USD 3.11 billion by 2030, growing at a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 6.5%. NPWTU is a medical device used to promote wound healing by applying controlled negative pressure to a wound. It is widely used in treating chronic wounds, surgical wounds, and traumatic wounds. The market is driven by the increasing prevalence of chronic diseases, the aging population, and advancements in wound care technology. The demand for advanced healthcare treatments is also contributing to market expansion. However, high treatment costs and lack of reimbursement in some regions could impede market growth.

